# Formatting (Prettier)

CI runs `npm run format:check`. All created or edited files must pass before you finish.

## Before finishing

1. Run `npm run format` on changed paths (or the whole repo if many files changed).
2. Run `npm run format:check` and fix any remaining warnings.
3. Do not hand-format — use Prettier so output matches `.prettierrc.json`.

## Common agent mistakes (Markdown / JSON)

- **Frontmatter**: No blank line between closing `---` and the first heading.
- **Lists after labels**: Add a blank line after `**Label**:` (or similar) before a bullet/numbered list.
- **Nested blocks**: Add a blank line before fenced code blocks inside list items.
- **JSON**: 2-space indent, trailing newline at EOF, no trailing commas (Prettier defaults).
- **Line endings**: Let Prettier normalize; do not mix manual CRLF/LF edits.

## TypeScript / TSX

- Tailwind classes in `className` are sorted by `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` — run format after editing class strings.
- Match existing quote style in the file; Prettier will normalize on format.

## Scope

Prettier checks the whole repo (see `.prettierignore` if present). New files under `.cursor/`, `.specify/`, `.github/`, and `specs/` are included — not just `src/`.
